23/02/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Noting that the election process is crucial for finalising a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU, Integration Minister Ermelinda Meksi expressed hope Tuesday (22 February) that the main political parties would quickly reach a final agreement on the new electoral map. The next meeting of the Albania-EU task force will take place in Brussels on Thursday.
In other news, unions representing teachers in higher education announced that a series of new protests will take place in March, if the government refuses to negotiate on the unions' demand for a salary increase. The unions have rejected a proposal to boost salaries by 11.4 per cent. (Albanian News - 23/02/05; ATA - 22/02/05)
